  "prompt": "Why won't Richard Muller answer my question?",
  "response": "Without specific details about the question you asked or the context in which you reached out to Richard Muller, it's difficult to provide a definitive answer. There could be several reasons why he hasn't responded:\n\n1. **Volume of Inquiries**: He may receive a large number of questions and may not have the time to respond to all of them.\n2. **Question Relevance**: The question may not align with his current work or interests, which might lead him to prioritize other inquiries.\n3. **Technical Jargon or Complexity**: If your question was particularly complex or technical, it may require more time to address than he currently has available.\n4. **Communication Method**: If you used a less direct method of communication (like social media or a general inquiry form), it might be easy for messages to get overlooked.\n\nIf you'd like a response, consider trying a different method to reach out, or make sure your question is clear and concise.",
